{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\n`test_leaves_registry_coverage.py::test_every_leaf_has_real_body` (`:83-100`) defines \"real\nbody\" as ≥3 AST statements OR a regex match for effect-shaped tokens (`client.`, `.append`,\n`subprocess.run`, …) over `inspect.getsource`. It passes while a leaf sends the WRONG target,\nDROPS a field, returns the WRONG follow-on, or SWALLOWS a required error — a structural proxy,\nnot behavior. VALIDATED.\n\n## What\nAdd a per-leaf behavioral effect matrix that drives each leaf in the `_LEAVES` registry with a\nmock Jira client and asserts its OBSERVABLE effect: the exact client/store call made (method +\nkey arguments), the returned `ApplyResult`, any follow-on effects, and its failure behavior.\n\nCompleteness (so coverage cannot silently lag the registry): the matrix is enumerated FROM\n`_LEAVES` itself (parametrize over `_LEAVES`), and a test asserts EVERY id in `_LEAVES` has a\nmatrix entry — a newly-added leaf with no behavioral entry fails that test.\n\nDo not blindly duplicate existing coverage: several leaves already have behavioral tests\nelsewhere (e.g. `test_apply_outbound_*`). Where a leaf is already behaviorally covered, the\nmatrix entry may be a thin assertion that references the same observable effect (or the\nexisting test is folded into the matrix) — the goal is one complete, enumerated behavioral\nmatrix over `_LEAVES`, not redundant tests. The AST heuristic, if kept, is RELABELED as an\nexplicitly-supplemental structural guard (not counted as behavioral coverage).\n\n## Scope\n- `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/orchestrate/test_leaves_registry_coverage.py` (and/or a new\n  per-leaf matrix module) — the behavioral matrix + the `_LEAVES`-completeness test.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] The behavioral matrix is enumerated from `_LEAVES`; a test asserts every `_LEAVES` id has\n      a matrix entry (a new uncovered leaf fails it).\n- [ ] Each leaf's entry asserts its observable effect via a mock Jira client: the exact\n      client/store call (method + key args) and the returned `ApplyResult`. Failure-behavior\n      coverage is quantified: EVERY leaf that has an error/exception path (raises, or returns a\n      failure/error-shaped `ApplyResult`) asserts that path's observable behavior; a leaf with\n      no error path asserts its success `ApplyResult` (and follow-ons, where it has any).\n- [ ] PROVING STEP with concrete evidence capture: pick one representative leaf, inject a\n      defect into its production body (wrong target entity, a dropped field, OR a wrong\n      follow-on), run that leaf's behavioral test, and CAPTURE the RED failure — record it as a\n      rebar comment on this ticket naming the leaf id, the exact defect injected, and the\n      failing assertion/output — THEN revert the defect (src/ left unchanged). The recorded RED\n      comment is the durable evidence that the matrix catches the failure mode; a green\n      `make test` after revert is necessary but, on its own, not sufficient.\n- [ ] If the AST heuristic is retained, it is relabeled as a supplemental structural guard, not\n      behavioral coverage.\n- [ ] `make lint && make test` green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783807064658564001,"uuid":"e49d6688-e7a5-4365-899d-2b854fe6d278"}